description.narrative: The prevalence of wasting in Somalia has persistently remained above 10% (serious) over the last 12 years underscores the need to strengthen coordinated multisectoral interventions. UNICEF has continued to support capacity building on the SUN initiative and establishment of multi-stakeholder platforms. Relatedly, UNICEF is leading the development of the Somali Nutrition Strategy aligned to the NDP and SDGs. The roll-out of the revised protocol for the integrated management of acute malnutrition (IMAM) aligned to WHO (2013) recommendations will ensure that children receive quality services for the treatment and care of acute malnutrition. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:31/12/2019
